by jrushlow at 2021-03-03T13:33:43Z

> AFAIK, shivammathur/setup-php can install older PHP versions on ubunut-20-04. What changes is which pre-installed version is available.

That is my understanding as well. We could continue to use the `ubuntu-latest` (20.04) then install php 7.1 - 7.3 and require the PDO extension. However using 18.04 negates the need to install the previous versions of PHP & the PDO extension.
